Cell.Text: I'm Tolan, a Vigilant of Stendarr. This was our hall, until the vampires attacked. Now it's nothing more than a ruin. | They came in the night. They slaughtered most of my brothers and sisters and ransacked our library. When they were done, they set the hall on fire.

Node.Caption: DLC01VQ01TolanOffersQuestTopic: Who are you? And what happened here?

Cell.Text: It was Brother Adalvald's journals they were after. He was a scholar. He wrote about vampires who have influenced Skyrim's history. | He was convinced there was some grand conspiracy at work. He became obsessed with ancient vampire artifacts and burial sites. | The rest of us always dismissed him as a bit of a crackpot, but if the vampires wanted his journals, then maybe there was something to it.

Node.Caption: DLC01VQ01TolanOffersQuest3: Any idea why they attacked you?

Cell.Text: [S] North, I think, then they turned west and that's the last I saw of them. | They mentioned some place called Dimhollow Crypt, but I don't know where that is.

Node.Caption: DLC01VQ01DeclineQuest: Did you see which way they went?

Cell.Text: [S] My nephew, Rian, had a better look than I did. You might ask him.

Because vampires, like the daedra, are the enemies of men. The Vigilants fight against evil in the name of Stendarr, lord of mercy. | And yet, these vampires seemed to be after something in particular. After killing my comrades, they began searching through our books and maps. | After that, they set fire to the hall. It was all I could do to crawl away in time.

Node.Caption: DLC01VQ01TolanOffersQuest2: Why would vampires attack your hall?

Cell.Text: Sent those fiends back to their graves, did you? Good. The spirits of my brothers and sister will rest more easily. | Did you learn why they stole Brother Adalvald's journal? What were they up to?

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ01TolanStage15ComebackTopic1: Those vampires won't be troubling you again

Cell.Text: Dimhollow Crypt? Brother Adalvald was there not long ago. Said he found something of great importance. | I suppose it was important to the vampires as well. | Whatever they were after, we have to beat them to it. I know I've asked much of you already, but I must ask more. | Are you willing to go back and try to figure out what they were looking for?

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ01TolanStage15ComebackTopic2: They were looking for something buried deep in a draugr crypt.

Cell.Text: I fear there's something larger at work here than it might seem. If only we had listened to Brother Adalvald's warnings.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ01TolanStage15CallbackTopic3: I'll see what I can find.

Cell.Text: [S] G|Stendarr bless you if you do.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ01TolanStage3BlockingTopic2: Let me see if I've got a healing potion.

Cell.Text: Wait, please! Don't leave me for the wolves to find!
I gave as good as I got, but the vampires got away.
[S] Thank you, my friend. If only you could cure my sorrow so easily.
The black-hearted cowards attacked in the night. By the time we woke up, they'd killed three men in their beds.
